HEADWORD: Emboil
<hw>Em*boil"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to boil with anger; to
irritate; to chafe.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

